headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell had eight of his 21 points in the fourth quarter and the Utah Jazz hit 19 3-pointers to beat the Boston Celtics 117-109 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell's 29, late 3 help Jazz beat Celtics 117-109

headlines.description: — The Miami Heat got another win, and for a change it came relatively easily.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 28, Heat stay hot with 113-98 win over Cavs

headlines.description: — Tobias Harris scored 30 points, Seth Curry had 20 and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the New York Knicks 99-96 on Tuesday night for their sixth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris leads 76ers to 6th straight win, 99-96 over Knicks

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 40 points on 15-for-20 shooting, and the Chicago Bulls beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 123-102 on Tuesday night for their second straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores 40 as Bulls beat Thunder 123-102

headlines.description: — Danilo Gallinari scored 20 of his 29 points in the first half and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Houston Rockets 119-107 on Tuesday night for their sixth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hawks beat Rockets 119-107; Houston drops 17th straight

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard had 50 points and 10 assists, and the Portland Trail Blazers came from behind to beat the New Orleans Pelicans 125-124 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard scores 50, Blazers rally past Pelicans 125-124

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 25 points, 12 rebounds and 12 assists in his 99th career triple-double, leading the Los Angeles Lakers to a 137-121 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron gets 99th triple-double, Lakers rout Wolves 137-121
